inn1.comm: full and coming in to the left hander just outside off, pushed to point
pakistan are underway, slides down leg and Butt trickles it down to fine leg
streaky, pitches on off and middle, slices Jamshed is sliced in half, he doesn't move his feet much and he gets a thin french cut that beats the stumps and rolls to fine leg
full and side outside the off stump, Jamshed leans forward and drives through the covers
good length outside off, gets the ball to bounce more, left alone
full and curving in on the pads, Jamshed works it though the line and guides it wide of mid-on
hits a good length on middle and leg, straightens, he covers the line and defends
slips this one in faster, lands on a full length outside off, Butt lets it go
holds the length back outside the off stump, goes back and pushes to the covers
much fuller, in the length to drive, But squeezes it out to cover
hits a good length on middle and leg, he goes back and defends
Butt leans forward to drive through the off side, he closes the face of the bat and drives back to the bowler
short and wide outside the off stump, Jamshed cuts to third man
half volley on middle and leg, Jamshed stays at the crease, lofts through the line and the ball sails over the bowler's head
Mpofu strays too wide outside off and gives Jamshed another gift, he stays back , cuts past point and the fielder at third man runs across and gives up the chase
bowls round the wicket this time, pitches it closer to the off stump, defended back to the bowler
grants him a bit of width outside off, Jamshed shapes to cut past point again but mistimes it, point dives to his right and cuts it off
chopped down just wide of the slips for a single
Chigumbura dislodges the bails at his end before delivery, Jamshed gets forward and defends
short and wide outside off, Jamshed spanks it past cover but there's protection for the bowler in the deep
aims for the yorker but slides it wide outside the line of off stump, Jamshed digs it out to point
this time Jamshed beats the off side field and fetches a single
pushed just wide of point for a single
Butt drives away from his body outside off and ends up getting an inside edge onto his body
just a little too wide outside off, in the slot to drive on the backfoot, punched to point
similar delivery, punched towards the covers
short of a length outside off, Jamshed rocks back and pulls in the vacant mid-on region, the fielder was pushed back
good length just outside off, Butt plays with an angled bat and slices past cover
fullish outside off, Jamshed drives on the up towards the covers
holds the length back outside the off stump, defended to the off side
the bowlers are sticking to the same line outside off, Butt cuts past the off side
full, wide and swinging away, Jamshed eyes a flashy boundary wide of point but misses, the ball kicks up a little after pitching and unsettles Jamshed
Jamshed stays back and defends solidly back to the bowler
pitches outside the off stump, Jamshed defends to the off side
full and wide outside off, driven firmly but short cover gets a hand to it
full and wide outside the off stump, Jamshed plays an expansive drive past the covers and the sweeper runs across and cuts it off
hits a good length on middle, Jamshed goes back and tucks it to the on side
pitched up outside off, in the slot to drive, Jamshed gets across and drives it firmly wide of mid-off
full and wider outside the off stump, he stretches out a little, meets the pitch of the ball and drives wide of extra cover
the slower ball, Jamshed gets a thin edge which goes to Taibu on the first bounce
pitches around the off stump, Jamshed defends to the off side
pitches outside the off stump, he stays back and punches it softly towards the covers
Butt plays with an angled bat and glides it just wide of point
the first of the series..... overpitched outside off, Jamshed waits on it, lofts through the line and clears the long-off fence
shortish outside the off stump, cuts just wide of point
Chigumbura breaks the stumps for the second time this morning, defended to mid-off
draws Butt forward, Butt takes his bottom hand off the bat and defends to cover

confusion.... full on middle, Butt nudges to square leg and takes off for a run, there was certainly a run in it but Jamshed wasn't interested, Butt has no time to turn back the fielder at square leg flings it to Taibu who fumbles, there was ample time for him to whip off the bails with Butt stranded in the other end
Chibhabha comes in Outside off stump, attempts a prod, Jamshed misses it
Overpitched outside off. Jamshed doesn't move his feet but gets hold off the ball and lobs it over the infield
Pitched on middle and tucked to the on side
Short of length, Jamshed twists and turns it to the on side
pitched outside off, yorker length, Jamshed opens the face of the bat trying to cut past slip fielder but it is intercepted
pitched on yorker length on middle and leg and new batsman Younis Khan digs it out
Younis gets forward and defends with soft hands
pitched outside off, Younis gets out and drives through the line towards cover
Full and outside off, he gets out again and taps it behind sqaure , looking for a run but has to scram back to the crease
Pitched outside off and defended to off side
Oversteps and pitches it outside off, ball dips in through the air and Younis blocks it
Free Hit pitches short outside off and Younis steps across the stumps and pulls. He mistimes the shot but it travels to the fielder at deep square leg
Pitches on a good length outside off and Jamshed flat-bats it to ocer the region of vacant mid-on
Pitched outside off, holds its line and Younis drives it
Pitched outside off and comes back, Younis starts to come forward bit stays back and inside-edges on to his pad. A big appeal turned down
Pitched outside off, goes wider and Younis drives through the covers for a boundary
Full and outside off and Younis defends
Chibhabha bowls this shorter but the line is wide and Younis rocks back to cut behind point
Jamshed gets his fifty with a six. Pitched short of good length and going outside off. Jamshed heaves it over long-off
Defended to the off side
half-volley outside off and Jamshed gets down on one knee to drive but can't penetrate the in-field
Jamshed is looking to up the run-rate. He looks to drive one going outside off and mistimes. He turns the face of the bat and mistimes to mid-on
Jamshed drives again but a good save by cover fielder converts a potential four into a single
Pitched fuller, outside off. Younisdrives it just wide of mid-off and takes off for a run. Mid-off fielder gets a direct hit at the non-striker's end but Younis is in
On the fuller length on middle and off and turns face of the bat and works it to midwicket
Younis stays at the crease and waits right till the ball is almost past him to cut it to third-man boundary
fullish  outside off and pushed to mid-off
A big appeal. Younis stays in the crease and the ball is almost on him when he puts his bat down on it. He may have inside-edged it on to his pads
Just short of length outside off and Jamshed swings across the line and lifts it way over midwicket
Slower ball, outside off. Jamshed stays at the crease and lofts it away from his body over the in-field. Lands safely close to the boundary
good length on off stump, comes in a little after pitching, Younis defends rather close to the pads
Younis walks across his stumps before the bowler lands the ball, it was premeditated, he tuns the face of the bat and lofts over mid-on, one bounce and four
defended to the off side
Younis walks across the stumps again, the ball lands outside off and he defends
pitches on a fuller length, walks across and picks the ball from outside off and glides it towards fine leg
slower ball outside off, he waits on it and cuts it to third man
Taibu stands upto the stumps, fuller outside off, pushed towards point, cramped for room
slower ball on middle, the ball doesn't come on quickly and Younis tucks it with soft hands to the on side
sprays wide outside off, Jamshed shapes to cut but the ball was well out of reach
adjusts the line closer to the off stumps, he gets behind the line and defends

cheap dismissal, Chibhabha bowls another slower one, the legcutter, the ball lands on a good length, Jamshed stays rooted to the crease, tries to loft over the bowler's head, he mistimes it and Matsikenyeri at long-off runs across to his right and takes it easily
pushed with soft hands to mid-off
hits a good length on off stump, cramps him for room, defended back to the bowler
hits a good length and gets it to cut back in from outside off, Younis has very little room to work with as he chops it down to the off side on the front foot
slides towards the pads, works it on its way to fine leg
sliding down the leg side again, tries to glance it fine but meets the ball on the body, Taibu dives to his left to cut it off
Dropped but an excellent attempt by Utseya, Younis walks across his stumps and tries to loft over mid-off, he doesn't get the elevation, Utseya nearly pulls off a one-handed blinder to his right
good length on middle, pushed to the on side
fullish on middle, pushed to mid-on
in the slot to drive outside off, Younis gets forward, drives uppishly but just beats cover to pick up three
Yousuf stays on the back foot and punches it to point
superb timing, just short of a length outside off, Yousuf transfers his weight on the back foot, opens the face of the bat and punches it wide of point and the ball scorches along the turf
slides down the leg side, wide called
good length outside off, stays back and punches to cover
angles in towards middle, Yousuf turns the face of the bat and pushes to midwicket
fuller in length on off and middle, gets forward and defends
doesn't impart any turn on this one, pitches on off, pushed just wide of cover
lands it in the line of off stump, pushed to mid-off
slower through the air, Yousuf opens the face and glides it to short third-man
fires it on a yorker length on off stump, Yousuf sqqeezes it back to the bowler
good length outside off, pushed to the off side
pitches outside off, Yousuf stays back but can't punch it past the infield on the off side
flighted on the pads, worked through the line to the off side
bowls over the wicket, lands it on a full length outside off, pushed to mid-off
flighted on leg, Yousuf uses his feet, gets to the pitch and lofts over mid-on
flighted on leg, worked through the on side
beaten, lands outside off and moves away, Younis gets cheeky and tries to cut a little close to his body
flighted on the pads, pushed to the on side
swings it in towards middle stump, pushed through the line to long-on
bowls this one wide outside off, Masakadza follows the batsman as he walks across his stumps, he checks his stroke and chops it to short third man
walks across his stumps again, Younis takes it on the full and pushes to long-on
sliding on the pads, worked through the line wide of square leg
low full toss outside off, Younis waits on it, gets on his knees and biffs it on the full over midwicket
full and wide outside off, he beats the infield on the off side and the ball races towards the extra cover boundary before being intercepted
flighted on off, switches to round the wicket, worked to the on side
turned behind square on the on side, the fielder has a shy at the strikers end but the batsmen makes it on time
attempts a sweep but is too late on the stroke, the ball clips the pads and rolls to the keeper
flighted outside the off stump, worked past point
floated outside off, driven through the line to long-off
pushed with soft hands on the front foot to the off side
flighted on the pads, he unfurls the reverse sweep but finds the fielder at short fine leg
flighted on the pads, worked to the on side
flighted outside off, cut to the off side
lands on a good length on middle, he rocks back and punches to long-on
flighted outside off, pushed to the off side
pushed back to the bowler
lands outside leg, comes in a little, tries to glance it fine but finds short fine-leg
another reverse sweep doesn't come out right as he finds point this time
flighted on middle and leg, worked to the on side
flighted on middle and leg, he waits on it and executes a controlled sweep, chips it high over square leg
slides down the leg side
stays back and chops it down towards cover, a slight fumbles allows for a run
shortish outside off, he stays back, plays with the turn and cuts past point
flighted outside leg, swept to fine leg
strays on the pads, he turns the face of the bat and glides it to the on side
gets this to loop in from outside off and into middle, lands on a fullish length, pushed back to the bowler
attempts a reverse sweep, checks his stroke and plays it back to the bowler
flighted on off and middle, Younis steps down the track, picks his gap and lofts over midwicket and the ball just falls short of the rope
pushed back to the bowler
lands on a good length on middle, he stays back and works it wide of midwicket
flighted on leg, worked through the line to the on side
classic.... flighted outside off, he stays at the crease, gets on his knee, meets the pitch of the ball and lofts over extra cover
flighted on leg, turned to the on side
defended back to the bowler
brings up his 30th ODI fifty with a boundary, flighted on middle and leg, he gets on his knee and sweeps wide of square leg, the ball races along the turf
goes downtown this time, flighted outside off, he takes a few paces forward, gets plenty of elevation and  lofts over the bowler's head
flighted on middle, pushed to the on side
tossed up on middle and leg, gets on his knee and sweeps
gives it a bit more air, he meets the ball on the full and punches to long-off
pitched full on leg stump, he plays through the line and works it to the on side
fullish on off stump, pushed back to the bowler
holds the length back outside off, Yousuf stays back and punches it back to the bowler
the slower ball, lands on middle, Yousuf turns the face of the bat and tucks it wide of midwickwet, they run the first one hard
drives away from his body and edges the ball onto his pads
pitches full outside off, pushed through the line to long-on
just a touch wide outside the off stump, he plays with an angled bat wide of point
steps down the track, he fires it on the blockhole outside off, the batsman diges it out to the off side
lands on a shortish length on leg, he swivels and pulls along the ground to deep square leg
another attempted reverse sweep which doesn't come off, he gets a thick top edge and the ball just falls short of short third man who dives to his right
flighted on leg, worked through the line to long-on
that was short of a length on leg and asking to be hit, Younis stays back, swivels and pulls over square leg and there were no red shirts in sight to cut it off
flighted on leg, pushed to the on side
pitches on middle and leg, worked to long-on
fullish outside the off stump, Yousuf lofts through the line over the off side, bisects the gap between long-off and deep extra cover
angling into the right hander, drops it with soft hands to the on side and sets off
slides down the leg side, worked through the line past square leg
lofted over midwicket, the ball runs towards the boundary but the fielder cuts it off
full and wide outside off, Younis gets forward, meets the pitch of the ball and places it perfectly past the covers
Opens the face of the bat and angles it down to third man
lands on middle and leg, he decides to stay back at the crease and punch to long-on
gets his front foot across his stumps, swings across the line to fine leg
flighted on the pads, turns the bat and works it with the line to the on side
flighted on leg again, all too easy for the batsman as he milks it past square leg for another easy single
pushed back to the bowler
tosses it very slowly on middle and leg, he tries to glance it fine but finds the fielder
pitches on a fullish length on leg, worked to the on side
juicy full toss, Yousuf stays at the crease and clubs it over midwicket, the placement wasn't perfect though
lands on a full length on middle, driven through the line to long-on
pushed in flat and fast outside off, he transfers his weight on the back foot and cuts to sweeper cover
chipped uppishly with soft hands towards midwicket, quick single taken

good judgment by Masakadza in the deep, Price bowls from over the wicket, flights it on leg, Younis goes for a premeditated slog sweep, the ball flies off the middle of the bat and Masakadza does well to time his dive forward at long leg and take it comfortably
tossed up outside off, pushed towards long-off
that's Yousuf's 61st ODI fifty, he brings up the landmark with a back foot punch to long-on
lands it on a good length on middle and leg, he rocks back and punches to long-on
sliding towards the pads, worked through the line towards fine leg
full outside off, in the slot to drive, he finds the fielder at cover
goes for the loft over mid-off, he mistimes it and the ball chips off the toe of his bat to short third-man
this time he gets the placement correct, flighted slowly on middle stump, backs away from the stumps, meets the pitch of the ball and lofts over cover
gives it plenty of air, Yousuf pushes the full toss past cover and a good stop at the boundary limits it to two runs
flighted on the pads, pushed towards midwicket
flighted on middle and leg, turned with soft hands in front of midwicket
flighted on the pads, swept to short fine leg
flighted outside off, pushed to the covers
gets a bit more drift into the right hands, Malik pushes it back to the bowler
floated outside the off stump, pushes though the line wide of mid-off
flighted on middle and leg, pushed in faster, he sweeps just in front of short fine leg and sets off, the stumps go down at the non-striker;s end but the batsman was home
flighted outside off, pushed to the off side
flighted on middle and leg, he turns his wrists and works it to long-on
gets a bit of turn into the right hander, he stays at the crease and punches to long-on
pushed just side of long-off, Utseya yells 'keeper, keeper'! to alert the fielder but the batsmen complete the second run easily
gets forward and pushes to the off side
turned to the on side
tossed up very slowly on middle stump, Malik steps down the track, lofts with the turn and deposits the ball over the deep midwicket rope
flighted on leg, he drives on the full to long-on
pushed in flatter and faster on the pads, tucked to the on side
steps down the track, picks it from the middle stump, doesn't time it as well but plays it down to long-on
attempts a sweep but misses it altogether
pitches outside off, defended to the off side
flighted on off stump, steps down the track, meets the pitch of the ball and lofts over long-off
flighted on off, defended to the off side
gives it plenty of air, meets it on the full  and pushes to short cover
flighted outside leg, tries to sweep but the ball lobs off his pads and rolls to the on side
chipped on the up back to the bowler, the ball just falls short of him
pitches short outside leg, Yousuf lofts on his knee towards long leg but doesn't time it well enough to reach the boundary
driven firmly back to the bowler
flighted ever so slowly, he steps down the track, theh checks his stroke and dabs it to short third-man
flighted on the pads, pushed to long-on
takes a few paces down the pitch, lofts down the region of the vacant mid-on region

a third prospective ton doesn't see the light of day, flighted on off and middle, he steps down and tries to loft over long-off, he doesn't get the desired elevation as Mpofu runs to his right and takes it with ease
flighted on leg, turned to the on side
lands on a full length on middle, turns his wrists and pushes it to long-on
full toss outside the off stump, he keeps it down and works it to long-off
pitches on a fullish length on the pads, turns his wrists and works it behind square on the on side
uses his feet, meets the ball on a fullish length and tucks it to midwicket
uses his feet again, worked to long-on
worked to deep square leg,  they contemplate a second run bu decide against it
the reverse sweep, Misbah gets in position for that stroke early, takes the ball on the full outside the leg stump, beats point and the sweeper cover
flighted outside the leg stump, pushed to long-on
flighted very slowly on middle, Misbah waits an eternity for it, adjusts his stroke, goes right back and pulls behind square
glanced towards short fine-leg, Misbah turns down the single
tossed up around the pads, turns his wrists and pushes to long-on
pushed to long-off, they blaze away for the first run and that allows the pair to complete the second fairly easily, Taibu yells 'keeper' but the throw was too late from the deep
pushed behind square on the on side for a single
waits on the back foot and punches to long off
good bowling, tosses it very slowly outside leg, Malik takes a few paces down, meets the ball close to his boot and pushes it tamely to long-on
straying on the pads, worked to deep midwicket for a couple, good running there
punched to long-off for a single
flighted outside the off stump, pushed to the off side
flighted outside the off stump, defended on the front foot
hits a good length outside off, gets it to cut back in, Misbah waits on it and plays a premeditated glide down to third man
fuller in length on middle, pushed towards midwicket
slower ball this time, the offcutter, Mpofu dives to his right as he tries to stop it and long-on does the fielding
the stump goes cartwheeling! at the non striker's end! Malik drives with brute force back past the bowler but the ball cannons onto the stump and sends it back a long way, that was a sure boundary
full on middle and leg, he shufles across his stumps but glances to short fine-leg
full and a touch too wide outside off, Malik drives firmly to the right of cover and nearly beats long-off who runs to his left and cuts it off
lands on a good length on leg, stays back and works it to long-on
tossed outside leg, he plays the reverse sweep but fails to beat the off side field
flighted on middle and leg, he turns the face of the bat and tucks it past square leg
played back to the bowler
fires it on a yorker length, he turns his wrists and tucks it to midwicket
pushed in flatter on leg stump, he rocks back and tucks it to midwicket
fullish outside the off stump, worked through the line towards mid-off
aims for a yorker on middle and off, Malik picks it on the full length, turns the face of the bat and works it past the vacant midwicket region
lands it on fullish length on middle and leg, Malik gets his wrists working again as he works it towards deep midwicket for another easy couple
slower ball, the off cutter lands outside the off stump, Malik angles it down to third man with an open faced of the bat
shorter in length outside off, Misbah waits for the ball, opens the face and dabs it with control past the wicketkeeper and down to third man
overpitched on middle stump, Malik stays at the crease, gets his bat under the ball and swings across the line, the ball is airborne over midwicket and reaches the boundary off the first bounce
full outside off, pushed towards mid-off
holds the length back outside off, punched back to the bowler, another dot ball
turned just wide of midwicket, they contemplate a second run but Misbah is sent back
punched down the ground to long-off
low full toss on middle and leg, pushed to long-on

oopsy, it slips out of his hand and heads towards Misbah's midriff, he moves away, plays if off the meat of the bat and glances it wide of short fine leg, umpire de Silva declares that a waist-height no ball
full on middle and leg, clipped to midwicket
just short and wide outside the off stump, Maliks rocks back and cuts to the sweeper cover
wide outside off, the bowler sees Malik walking across his stumps and chases him, he ends up spraying that way too wide for Malik to get a faint touch to it
risky run, clipped to midwicket for a quick single and Misbah was a little too slow to get off the blocks there
glanced down to fine leg for a single and that brings up Pakistan's 300
pushed to long-off and Malik signals his return from injury with a fifty, his 25th in ODIs, Well done, skipper
full on middle and leg, closes the face of the bat and whips to midwicket
he oversteps, an attempted yorker on leg turns into a low full toss, he works it through the line and bisects the gap between midwicket and long-on
short of a length on leg, he rocks backwards and pulls with force over deep square leg
fullish outside off, lofted through the line over mid-off
full outside off, worked past extra cover
full on the pads, worked to square leg for a single
full on middle, Malik gets down on his knee and lofts it over the bowler's head, the timing wasn't right as the fielder runs across and cuts it off
pushed down towards deep backward point
swinging in down the leg side, Misbah fails to get any wood on it as he tries to glance and Taibu does well to fling himself to his left and stop a certain four
full on middle and leg, pushed softly to long-on, they set off quickly and that allows them to come back for the second
full outside off, he gives room and digs it out behind square on the off side
Malik tries to club it away across the line but mistimes it, the ball falls well short of the fielder at deep midwicket
full on the leg stump, driven down the ground to long-on
low full toss on middle and leg, picked on the full and there;s more work for long-on
another attempted yorker turns into a low full toss, Misbah lofts off the toe edge of the bat towards long-on, the fielder makes a brave attempt at catchig it but the ball just falls short of him
high full toss this time, Misbah was a few yards down the track before clubbing the ball over midwicket
better delivery, pitches on a fuller length, pushed to the of side
another yorker turns into a full toss, a high one that too, Malik clubs that over deep backward square leg
Malik stays at the crease and goes for the loft over long-on, he fails to connect off the meat of the bat and ends up hitting down Masakadza;s throat at long-on
slides down the leg side, the crowd roar at the sight of Afridi
goes on the back foot and works it to deep midwicket
that was short and wide outside the off stump, Misbah stays on the back foot, picks his spot and bashes it along the ground past extra cover
hits the blockhole outside the off stump, Misbah gets his bat down and digs it out to long-off
lands it on the blockhole again, he kees Afridi quiet as he manages only a single to the off side
full outside off, he makes room to crash the ball over the off side field but can't bisect the gap between long-off and deep extra cover
bangs it in short on middle and leg, the ball climbs on Afridi, he ducks thinking it would be declared a wide but umpire Haider is satisfied with that

inn2.comm: swings it away from the right hander, goes through to Akmal at waist height, left alone
this one pitches on off and swings away just a tad, not too far from the wood there, well left though
swings wider outside the off stump, Sibanda lets it go again
pitches on off and shapes away, left alone safely
pitches outside the off stump and the ball holds its line through to the keeper, Tanvir doesn't make him play
he bends this one into the right hander, gets Sibanda forward to defend

that was a close call for leg before! pitches on middle and straightens, catches the batsman on the back foot, the ball strikes him high on the pad, Niazi appeals but the ball may have struck him just over the stumps
pitches on middle, Masakadza turns his wrists and whips it behind square on the on side
pitches on middle again on a good length, he uses his wrists again and works it wide of midwicket this time
fuller in length on off stump, Sibanda doesn't cover the line properly and defends with an angled bat back to the bowler
this time Sibanda defends solidly back to the bowler
Zimbabwe are underway, fullish on the off stump, Sibanda turns his wrists and flicks it with control, chips over midwicket
pitches outside off and shapes away from the right hander
pitches outside off and shapes away from the right hander, Masakadza shoulders arms again
gets the ball to bend back in and make him play, he keeps it down to the on side
just short of a driveable length outside the off stump, Sibanda drives uppishly towards point
struggles to control the outswing, the ball drifts further away from the right hander and wide called

pitches it a little too full and wide outside the off stump, Sibanda gets a good stride across and chips uppishly past the covers, it appeared as if he would spoon it to the fielders but the placement was just right
defended back to the bowler
hits a good length outside the off stump, pushed back to the bowler
hits a good length on off and middle, tucked back to the bowler
hits a good length closer to leg stump, he tries to whip it wide of midwicket but finds the fielder
good length on middle and leg, pushed to the on side
pitches just outside the off stump, Masakadza has a feel at it and the ball catches the outside edge, beats the slips and runs down to third man
good length outside off, no swing for Khan, left alone
fullish outside the off stump, chopped down to the covers
tries something different, pitches outside leg but the ball straightens, he goes for the leg glance and misses
lands it on a good length on off stump this time, pushed to the covers
tempts him with width outside off, he goes for the flashy drive and misses it completely
fullish in length outside the off stump, pushed just wide of mid-on for a single
slides towards the pads, Sibanda works his wrists and turns it to midwicket
Tanvir struggles with his line again, slides down the leg side and Akmal has a bit of work to do behind the stumps
turned just wide of midwicket for a single
bangs it in short outside off, the ball kicks on him and Akmal takes it high over his head, the umpire signals a wide
pushed firmly to short cover, Afridi does well to get across to his left and get a hand to it
pushed with soft hands in front of mid-off, quick single taken
Khan errs with his line, drifts too wide outside the off stump, Sibanda picks it off a good length, drives through the line and bisects the gap between cover and extra cover

superb stroke, that was much fuller outside the off stump, Sibanda gets forward, shows the full face of the bat and drives past the bowler, the ball scorches along the turf and there was no chance of mid-off getting a hand to it
pushed in front of mid-off for another quick single
punched straight to Jamshed at short cover
misfield, Sibanda cuts to Butt at point and a fumble costs a single
grants him a bit of width outside the off stump, he chops it down to Butt at point again
defended back to the bowler
